Book of Hours, Use of Rome ("Marquand Hours")

Bryn Mawr College Library, MS 25. Piedmont, Italy, Fourth quarter 15th century. This is a book of hours from the fourth quarter of the fifteenth century from Italy, Use of Rome. There are eleven full-page miniatures surrounded by full borders, which include the full Infancy cycle for the Hours of the Virgin, as well as miniatures for the Short Hours of the Cross and the Short Hours of the Holy Spirit. Previous owners include the Discalced Augustinians of San Carlo, Turin in the eighteenth century,  Eleanor Cross Marquand, and Allan P. Marquand.
